The article announces the release of Reuters journalists Wa Lone and Kyaw Soe Oo, who were pardoned by Burma's civilian government. The journalists had been imprisoned for over 500 days for reporting on atrocities against the Rohingya. The article expresses delight that they will be reunited with their families and hopes that other jailed journalists in Burma will also be freed. It emphasizes the importance of a free press, freedom of religion, and the rule of law for a democracy. The United States pledges to continue promoting stability, prosperity, and democratic transition in Burma.